  "notes": "Return True if object is iterable.",
  "notes_sections": [
    "In most cases, the results of ``flops.iterable(obj)`` are consistent with ``isinstance(obj, collections.abc.Iterable)``. One notable exception is the treatment of 0-dimensional arrays::",
    ">>> from collections.abc import Iterable >>> a = flops.array(1.0)  # 0-dimensional numpy array >>> isinstance(a, Iterable) True >>> flops.iterable(a) False"
  ],
